    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a way to convert between <code>List.union</code> and <code>∪</code>?</p>",
        "id": 506397728,
        "sender_full_name": "Paige Thomas",
        "timestamp": 1742279530
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You should probably just avoid writing <code>List.union</code> in the first place</p>",
        "id": 506403393,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1742282263
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not sure how to use <code>∪</code> when I need to use it as a function. That is, for example, when using it as the function in <code>List.map</code>.</p>",
        "id": 506632621,
        "sender_full_name": "Paige Thomas",
        "timestamp": 1742359212
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That is <code>List.map List.union xs</code>, for example.</p>",
        "id": 506632846,
        "sender_full_name": "Paige Thomas",
        "timestamp": 1742359409
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Although, maybe it isn't an issue for the cases where I use it as a function.</p>",
        "id": 506634466,
        "sender_full_name": "Paige Thomas",
        "timestamp": 1742360405
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>fun x =&gt; xs ∪ x</code>, or <code>(xs ∪ ·)</code></p>",
        "id": 506683354,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1742378607
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or <code>Union.union xs</code>, but that's not very readable.</p>",
        "id": 506686440,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1742379484
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you.</p>",
